{"TopicId":138424,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"(Edit) Four Laser Guide Star Facility in the Atacama","CreatedByName":"Glaran K\u0026#039;erman","CreatedById":146334,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T04:32:36Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Glaran K\u0026#039;erman","CreatedById":146334,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T04:32:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Four Laser Guide Star Facility in the Atacama Desert\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nImages from Space.com article\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.space.com/32724-awesome-very-large-telescope-lasers-photos.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehere\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022paranal-observatory-laser-guide-system.j\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.space.com/images/i/000/055/096/original/paranal-observatory-laser-guide-system.jpg?1461806946?interpolation=lanczos-none\u0026amp;downsize=*:1400\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022paranal-observatory-first-light.jpg?inte\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.space.com/images/i/000/055/095/original/paranal-observatory-first-light.jpg?interpolation=lanczos-none\u0026amp;downsize=*:1400\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022paranal_observatory_laser_optics.jpg?146\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.space.com/images/i/000/055/097/i02/paranal_observatory_laser_optics.jpg?1461807266?interpolation=lanczos-none\u0026amp;downsize=640:*\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe laser helps to calibrate the adaptive optics by frying atoms. Do not place hand in front of laser.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-29T22:02:17Z\u0022 title=\u002204/29/2016 10:02  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 29, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Glaran K\u0026#039;erman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Streetwind","CreatedById":98962,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T07:58:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe best way to get there is probably by plane or helicopter. Not sure what that has to do with the posted content though... unless you really want to place your hand in front of that laser.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerbMav","CreatedById":70338,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T08:43:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAhm ... are the beams really THAT visible?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T10:02:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, it does. Otherwise no AO system as they relied on the false star created by the beam. Though possibly it\u0027s a long exposure so reduce the magnitude a bit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat being said, best way to get there... Go with a tour group ? Or apply as ESO researcher but that also requires decent knowledge of the things.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-29T10:04:16Z\u0022 title=\u002204/29/2016 10:04  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 29, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by YNM\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RainDreamer","CreatedById":129077,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T10:54:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow I want a\u00A0version of that in KSP\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PB666","CreatedById":107380,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T16:23:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome poor alien wondering whether or not to fry the planet earth just got its eye\u0027s fried. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kryten","CreatedById":348,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T16:31:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222547768\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022138424\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461919399\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270338\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KerbMav\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, KerbMav said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAhm ... are the beams really THAT visible?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope. It\u0027s clearly a long exposure/contrast-stretched/both, just look how many stars there are and how bright the background colour is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sevenperforce","CreatedById":157695,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T17:31:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222548518\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022138424\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461947470\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kryten\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Kryten said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope. It\u0027s clearly a long exposure/contrast-stretched/both, just look how many stars there are and how bright the background colour is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut not too long or the stars would be star trails.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AngelLestat","CreatedById":58968,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T17:44:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nforget it, already answered.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-04-29T17:45:24Z\u0022 title=\u002204/29/2016 05:45  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EApril 29, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by AngelLestat\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Glaran K\u0026#039;erman","CreatedById":146334,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-04-29T18:03:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry if thread title is misleading, just joking about how cool it would be to see this place\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lajoswinkler","CreatedById":79159,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-01T10:27:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222548630\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022138424\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221461951107\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157695\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sevenperforce\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/29/2016 at 7:31 PM, sevenperforce said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut not too long or the stars would be star trails.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s why we use more sensitive sensors, to cut down the exposure time and get the same thing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, I wonder how do they keep the sharks so still...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RainDreamer","CreatedById":129077,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-01T10:37:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222552593\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022138424\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462098477\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002279159\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022lajoswinkler\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, lajoswinkler said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, I wonder how do they keep the sharks so still...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey don\u0027t.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nInstead they use microscopic laser sharks inside tiny tanks, and what we see is actually created from vicious battles\u00A0between these sharks for dominance, their laser captured by optics and combined into the beams we see.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shpaget","CreatedById":45577,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-01T10:44:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s entirely possible\u00A0and, I\u0027d say, quite likely\u00A0that the images were produced from multiple stacked shots.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Delfinus","CreatedById":154315,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-02T05:13:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat would happen if you did place your hand in front of the laser?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shpaget","CreatedById":45577,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-02T05:26:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222554829\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022138424\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221462166030\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154315\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DolphinDude3\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, DolphinDude3 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat would happen if you did place your hand in front of the laser?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.eso.org/sci/facilities/develop/4LGSF.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.eso.org/sci/facilities/develop/4LGSF.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe site quotes the laser power as 22 W, which is a fair bit, however, \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laser_guide_star\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EWikipedia article\u003C/a\u003E also states that the diameter of each of the laser beams is 30 cm. That means it would be perfectly safe to place your hand in front of it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t point the beam\u00A0directly into your eyes, though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}